{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop means-testing heating oil support",
        "additional_details": "The Government has announced support for heating-oil households, but this is means-tested.\r\nHeating-oil users should be treated fairly and receive equivalent support or protections, and not be disadvantaged for living off the gas grid.\r\nWe want the Government to provide non-means-tested support.",
        "background": "We want the Government to provide heating-oil support that is not means-tested. Around 1.5m UK households rely on heating oil. Unlike gas & electricity users, they aren\u2019t protected by the energy price cap and must often pay large upfront costs.",
